OL,3,CNew guidance as ministers 'ban' mobile
OL,4,Cphones in schools
OL,6,FIt is currently up to individual head
OL,7,Fteachers to decide their own policies
OL,8,Fon mobile phones and whether they
OL,9,Fshould be banned.
OL,11,FThe guidance, which is non-statutory,
OL,12,Finstructs headteachers on how to ban
OL,13,Fthe use of phones not only during
OL,14,Flessons but during break and lunch
OL,15,Fperiods as well.
