OL,6,F"We have lost count of the number of
OL,7,Ftimes that ministers have now
OL,8,Fannounced a crackdown on mobile phones
OL,9,Fin schools. It is a non-policy for a
OL,10,Fnon-problem.
OL,12,F"The Government would be far better
OL,13,Foff putting its energies into bringing
OL,14,Fto heel the online platforms via which
OL,15,Fchildren are able to access disturbing
OL,16,Fand extreme content."
OL,18,FJason Elsom, chief executive of
OL,19,FParentkind said: "The government is
OL,20,Fright to be taking decisive action on
OL,21,Fthe use of phones in schools.
